https://i.pinimg.com/originals/c8/e5/21/c8e5212b892539dfe153dc0cc73e1543.jpg";s:8:"filetype";s:4:"jpeg";s:5:"width";i:1440;s:6:"height";i:810;s:6:"source";s:48:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/582934745509352092";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}i:23;a:10:{s:7:"keyword";s:35:"garden route south africa itinerary";s:4:"slug";s:35:"garden-route-south-africa-itinerary";s:5:"title";s:56:"A Perfect South Africa Itinerary 2 Weeks or Less in Cape";s:3:"alt";s:56:"A Perfect South Africa Itinerary 2 Weeks or Less in Cape";s:3:"url";s:76:"https://i.pinimg.com/originals/a9/ca/9e/a9ca9eed40118cec8f40ea4a0f9f2202.jpg";s:8:"filetype";s:4:"jpeg";s:5:"width";i:735;s:6:"height";i:1102;s:6:"source";s:47:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/35677022036726645";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:7:"related";a:0:{}s:9:"sentences";a:62:{i:0;s:104:"But for the purpose of this blog post, this itinerary will start in cape town and end in port elizabeth.";i:1;s:119:"The one route that i would recommend to most people ( especially if you are a flashpacker like me) is the garden route.";i:2;s:124:"It gets its name from the lush and ecologically diverse vegetation and numerous lagoons and lakes scattered about the coast.";i:3;s:100:"This route is one of the most famous auto routes in south africa and also one of the most beautiful.";i:4;s:76:"A popular tourist destination, the route stretches for about 300 km (186 mi.";i:5;s:101:"Check out our tips for accommodation, activities, safaris, routes and for going off the beaten track.";i:6;s:190:"It is known to be one of the most famous road trips in the world, definitely an african bucket list activity, which is why i wanted to share my comprehensive garden route itinerary with you.";i:7;s:105:"If you are planning the ultimate south african road trip, then you just have to include the garden route.";i:8;s:99:"There is a bunch of exciting routes and itineraries you can choose from when visiting south africa.";i:9;s:84:"Garden route | this iconic route takes you along one of the world's best coastlines;";i:10;s:92:"Geographically the garden route is a 300 kms stretch between mossel bay to the storms river.";i:11;s:135:"Firstly we got to experience the top things to do in cape town before driving out to wineries and coastal drives down the garden route.";i:12;s:321:"If you planning your south africa holiday, you simply can’t go wrong with the garden route.officially running along the n2 from cape town to mossel bay and then along the coast to port elizabeth, this tour will give you extra stops along the way to make sure you get the absolute best from your south africa road trip!.";i:13;s:153:"Turns out, the garden route in south africa is a 300 km stretch of land along the southwestern coast of south africa between capetown and port elizabeth.";i:14;s:98:"Being so close to cape town, most trips to the garden route will either start or end in this city.";i:15;s:127:"South africaâ€™s garden route stretches along the coast from mossel bay on the west side to storms river on the east side.";i:16;s:184:"The garden route runs along south africa’s southern coast from the town of mossel bay all the way to eastern cape, and it’s a fantastic addition to a 2 week south africa itinerary!";i:17;s:113:"The garden route is a scenic stretch along south africa’s east coast, reaching from storms river to mossel bay.";i:18;s:93:"A lot of people begin their drive in cape town and head towards port elizabeth or vise versa.";i:19;s:33:"There's no wonder it's so famous.";i:20;s:93:"More officially, the garden route actually starts in mossel bay (387km outside of cape town).";i:21;s:85:"Ironically, the garden route is actually one of the best coastal drives in the world.";i:22;s:69:"Exploring the garden route en route from port elizabeth to cape town.";i:23;s:195:"There are many scenic drives in south africa, such as the iconic panorama route in south africa’s mpumalanga province.however, the garden route is one of the most popular and for a good reason.";i:24;s:70:"From cape town we’ll be adding in a wine tour in stellenbocsh, cage.";i:25;s:137:"The garden route, a popular road trip destination in south africa, is often considered one of the most beautiful road trips in the world.";i:26;s:104:"Technically, the garden route stretches 200 km, from mossel bay in the west to storms river in the east.";i:27;s:180:"Obviously one could spend far longer than 6 days driving along the garden route but for a two week itinerary of all of south africa, this will be enough to see the main highlights.";i:28;s:170:"The garden route owes this name to an enormously varied landscape of half desert, colorful pine forests, lush deciduous forests, rocky mountains and beautiful coastlines.";i:29;s:127:"A decade later, when vid and i finally embarked on our road trip through south africa, i was sure i wanted to visit oudtshoorn.";i:30;s:146:"There are many spots to visit on this road trip, so planning your garden route itinerary can be a bit daunting if you don’t know where to begin.";i:31;s:90:"Depending on time in hand you can spend anywhere between 5 to 10 days to cover this route.";i:32;s:81:"Technically, mossel bay is the beginning of the garden route (more on the garden.";i:33;s:223:"Create a fully customized day by day itinerary for free hike or drive the southeastern coast of south africa along garden route, a stretch of coastland with a remarkable range of plants, numerous lagoons, lakes, and trails.";i:34;s:24:"Map of the garden route.";i:35;s:86:"I can’t think of a better place to start your garden route, south africa, itinerary.";i:36;s:60:"It has forests, mountains, lagoons, grasslands, and deserts.";i:37;s:69:"It’s also naturally beautiful, nestled between mountains and ocean.";i:38;s:153:"It includes towns such as hermanus, mossel bay, knysna, oudtshoorn, george, plettenberg bay, nature’s valley, jeffrey’s bay, port elizabeth and addo.";i:39;s:59:"Backpacking in style across the garden route, south africa:";i:40;s:126:"The garden route south africa itinerary we spent two weeks in south africa self driving the garden route completely unplanned!";i:41;s:54:"You can of course start the route in either direction.";i:42;s:97:"If you’re planning a trip to south africa, adding the garden route to your itinerary is a must.";i:43;s:33:"Garden route road trip itinerary.";i:44;s:81:"Starting from wine country, i went great white shark diving early in the morning.";i:45;s:153:"Along the southern coast of south africa, nearly as close to antarctica as you can get with a car runs a 300km stretch of road known as the garden route.";i:46;s:54:"Here is how to spend two weeks traveling south africa.";i:47;s:90:"South africa is such a wild place to visit, and the garden route is one of its best spots.";i:48;s:222:"The garden route is also one of the most popular activities for visitors to south africa as it provides an opportunity to visit many incredible beaches, forests, mountains and parks along the southern coast of the country.";i:49;s:117:"Though it isn’t technically part of the garden route, i’m including the town of hermanus in this section as well.";i:50;s:216:"A drive covering the garden route in south africa has no doubt been one of the most picturesque drives of our lives.there is so much to see and experience on this route that it’s difficult to stick to an itinerary.";i:51;s:156:"Golden sands, frontier towns, craftsmen's houses and vast national parks, and generally speaking, the natural beauty is dialled up to ten wherever you look.";i:52;s:87:"The garden route south africa has a lot to offer for families and individual travelers.";i:53;s:160:"After our amazing safari trip we flew from johannesburg to port elizabeth where we spent the night before setting off the next day along ‘the garden route’.";i:54;s:57:"Plan your perfect garden route itinerary in south africa.";i:55;s:237:"Known as the garden route, the road trip gets its name from the garden route national park that it covers, and the diverse vegetation and wildlife, and abundance of lagoons, lakes, mountains, forests, and beaches along its winding roads.";i:56;s:129:"We spent a fortnight exploring the garden route’s sandy beaches, turquoise lagoons, wildlife reserves, and untamed countryside.";i:57;s:70:"In some ways, the garden route is a condensed version of south africa:";i:58;s:122:"Driving south africa’s garden route is one of the best ways to experience the natural beauty of that incredible country.";i:59;s:84:"The route technically starts at mossel bay and runs to the storms river in the east;";i:60;s:61:"Thus, the garden route was firmly pencilled on our itinerary.";i:61;s:141:"And that, my friends, is the full story of my garden route itinerary — seven essential days, plus five additional days of worthwhile stops.";}}